    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-11-11T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-11-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="246"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d246">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Persian Chargé d’Affaires</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_KKA1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kuli Kahn</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <dateline>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                    <placeName>
                        <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                    </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-11-11">
                        <hi rend="italic">November 11, 1914</hi>.</date>
                </dateline>
                <p rend="flushleft">No. 2]</p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt of
                    your note of November 6, 1914, giving the English translation of a cable message
                    received by you from His Excellency the Persian Minister for Foreign Affairs
                    requesting that this Government use its good offices with other powers looking
                    to the preservation of the neutrality of Persia.</p>
                <p>In reply I have the honor to inform you that the Government of the United States
                    will lend its good offices to assist in doing whatever it may properly do to
                    alleviate the conditions resulting from the situation existing in Europe.</p>
                <p>Accept [etc.]</p>
                <closer>For the Secretary of State: <lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
